{"type":"message","id":"9707a347","parentId":"f61d5bb5","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:15:20.935Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No session-summary files exist! The hook should have created one. Let me check:\n1. Did the session-summary hook fire for the previous session?\n2. Is the hook enabled and configured correctly?\n\nThe ephemeral directory is in `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/` (not in the workspace main directory). Let me check where the ephemeral files are:\n\nWait, I see the files are at `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ephemeral/`. The ls shows files there. But the session-summary hook looks for ephemeral at `workspace/memory/ephemeral` relative to the workspace. \n\nI need to trace through the hook's logic more carefully. The session-summary hook runs on /new or /reset commands, so when the current session started, it should have generated a summary for the previous one. But there's no summary file to show for it.\n\nLooking at the ephemeral data, the 20:47 file is substantial at 61KB—that's the session where we discussed context management. Either the hook didn't trigger, or it generated a summary but stored it somewhere unexpected.","thinkingSignature":"828a6f0cfa6984e6cd93de52c5152b73fcc176f72dc9e2780aea96c7713f04d2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qeigd4epi5yt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/workspace/main/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qeigd4epi5yt_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw hooks list 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/config.json 2>/dev/null | grep -A10 \"hooks\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26064,"output":325,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45651,"cost":{"input":0.0078192,"output":0.00039,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009364919999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":177