{"type":"message","id":"2e45bc20","parentId":"92d0dc9e","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:15:38.880Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d6c1n3qg779g_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HOOK.md\nauto-score-classify\ncontext-hook.js\nhandler.js\nhandler.ts\non-command-error.sh\non-message.sh\nself-improvement.js\nsession-summary\n---\n/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":56,"aggregated":"HOOK.md\nauto-score-classify\ncontext-hook.js\nhandler.js\nhandler.ts\non-command-error.sh\non-message.sh\nself-improvement.js\nsession-summary\n---\n/**\n * Context Hook for OpenClaw\n * \n * 监听消息事件，自动调用保护层context模块\n * \n * 支持的事件:\n * - message:receive: 用户发送消息\n * - message:send: AI 发送消息\n * - agent:response: Agent 回复\n */\n\nconst handler = async (event) => {\n  try {\n    // 检查是否有全局上下文接口\n    if (!global.openclaw || !global.openclaw.addContextMessage) {\n      // 尝试加载保护层\n      try {\n        const protection = await import(process.env.HOME + '/.openclaw/protection/index.js');\n        await protection.default.init();\n      } catch (e) {","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/main"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776172538872}}
{"type":"message","id":"71d92939","parentId":"2e45bc20","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:15:50.439Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context-hook.js looks like it tries to use a protection layer. The session-summary hook isn't creating files. Let me investigate why.\n\nThe key question: Did the session-summary hook run when `/new` was triggered at 20:44? The current session started with a /new. The previous session ended at around 20:50 (when we discussed context management). The hook fires on `command:new` or `command:reset`.\n\nBut the ephemeral files show:\n- 2026-04-14-12.jsonl at 20:47 (61KB) - this is the context management discussion session\n- 2026-04-14-13.jsonl at 21:08 (1KB) - this is the current session after /new\n\n\nSo when /new was triggered at 20:44, it should have fired the session-summary hook for the previous session (the one with the context management discussion), yet there's no output file. The hook is probably failing silently. Looking at the hook code, it searches for session files in the sessions directory using session IDs, but webchat sessions might not generate .jsonl files like other session types do, which could be causing the lookup to fail.\n\nThe hook tries to build a fallback path through the sessions directory when sessionFile isn't available in the context. I need to figure out where the actual session data is stored and whether it's accessible to the hook when it's running.","thinkingSignature":"10c21f6668a849e41f4ff9c755ce05b26134a30bb030f0281bd65ba2ead08af0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oqz9hsn92ls5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.jsonl\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"node_modules\\|ephemeral\" | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oqz9hsn92ls5_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/sessions/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/sessions/agent\\:main\\:main/context.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27292,"output":419,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46973,"cost":{"input":0.0081876,"output":0.0005028,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00984612}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776172538881,"responseId":"062d70faa827dc37aa1ba3784508fe7d"}}
