{"type":"message","id":"96427df5","parentId":"070bc948","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:16:14.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The session files are in `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/`, not `~/.openclaw/sessions/`. The session-summary hook looks in `~/.openclaw/sessions/` (the bundled hook's `findPreviousSessionFile` looks there).\n\nLet me look at the hook's session resolution logic more carefully. The handler.js has two functions:\n1. `resolveSessionFile` - from the bundled session-memory hook, looks in sessionsDir\n2. `findPreviousSessionFile` - also looks in sessionsDir\n\nBut the actual session data is in `agents/main/sessions/`. This is the core bug - the hook is looking in the wrong directory.\n\n\nI need to trace through the actual hook code to see where this mismatch originates. Looking at the session-summary hook, it should be pulling from the bundled hooks in `~/.openclaw/hooks/session-summary/` but the session data is stored in a completely different path under agents. The bundled hook that should be there isn't, which is why the lookup is failing. The hook's `resolveSessionFile` function is trying to resolve session files, but it's looking in the wrong directory—the actual session data lives in `agents/main/sessions/` while the hook searches `sessions/`. There's also a `workspaceDir` variable being constructed that might be pointing to the correct location, so I need to trace through whether that's actually being used or if the wrong path is taking precedence.\n\nLooking at the `findPreviousSessionFile` function, it's doing file matching and canonicalization in the `sessions/` directory, but the real session files are stored under `agents/main/sessions/`. The hook was apparently working before since there are ephemeral files with sessionKeys, but those came from the ephemeral hook running during the session itself, not from the session-summary hook successfully reading session data.\n\nThe core problem is that the session-summary hook is searching in the wrong location for session files. The webchat session has context that includes session entry information, but the hook's session file resolution logic isn't finding what's actually there.","thinkingSignature":"d72f48aa189a331f4196b48658647abe75b7a6c0fa53f80d7c89af5dfcce9f6a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gs318vp1g38z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/db92e41d-6d9e-4a84-9c19-4792adcfc0d0.jsonl 2>/dev/null | head -3 | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -20; echo \"---\"; ls -la ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ | grep \"Apr 14 20\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29324,"output":527,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49113,"cost":{"input":0.0087972,"output":0.0006324,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010585319999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776172557952,"responseId":"062d710d384c523ab6e54e88ad5133be"}}
