{"type":"message","id":"ed382116","parentId":"2e937cb5","timestamp":"2026-04-14T13:20:38.188Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - there's a reset file from April 6 and the latest active file is from today (Apr 14). The session from the webchat earlier today (Apr 14 20:42) was reset - I can see `39810b86-05f6-4394-88dd-9c3b62eec68e.jsonl.reset.2026-04-14T12-44-13.936Z` in the list.\n\nBut the latest reset by mtime is not the Apr 14 one - the Apr 14 reset is from `ls -lt` which showed the Apr 14 one at the top. Wait, `sort().reverse()[0]` sorts alphabetically in reverse, so it's getting the lexicographically latest, not the most recent by mtime.\n\n\nActually, lexicographic sorting would put `f60ee92c...` at the top since it starts with 'f' while the Apr 14 one starts with '3', so that's consistent with the output. The `sort().reverse()[0]` approach sorts lexicographically in descending order rather than by mtime, so it's picking the alphabetically latest filename, not the most recently modified file.","thinkingSignature":"1982aeb4afaa32c530786f56b5e2c749a67ad3422be8704d710467c26d4b149e"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了。当前活跃 session 文件是 `fbd49ab5-*.jsonl`，上一个（Apr 14 20:42 reset 的）是 `39810b86-...-reset.2026-04-14T12-44-13.936Z`。\n\nhook 修复逻辑能覆盖这个场景。下次 `/new` 时会找到正确的 reset 文件并生成摘要。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":35376,"output":324,"cacheRead":19262,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54962,"cost":{"input":0.0106128,"output":0.00038879999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011557199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01215732}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776172829419,"responseId":"062d721c12e55080e1632b2771f6f86c"}}
